spirit:component.spirit:description: The IP 10G Ethernet Subsystem provides a 10Gbps Ethernet MAC and PCS/PMA in BASE-R/KR modes, designed to the IEEE802.3 specification. The transmit and receive data interfaces use AXI4-Stream interfaces. An optional AXI4-Lite interface is used for the control interface to internal registers. The core can also provide optional high accuracy IEEE1588-2008 1-step and 2-step hardware time-stamping for BASE-R permutations.
